column2: Note that this run produced an exeptionally large data volume (1400 GB instead of typical 350 GB). This is because Suji was not elaborate on all Illumina settings. We might be able to save same space by removing / compressing certain files. But I (Stefan Janssen) have not yet done so.
I manually changed barcodes for lane3 following Sujis advice. But this comes with the very high risk of introducing a sample swap.
